{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761475173,"sessionID":"ses_126bf2c73ffeZ1nadU7aA32XcF","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_xGidTntlYUk6IiHH3fheXhmV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"context-server|model-server-supervision|socket-server|spec-memory.cjs","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit","include":"*.{js,ts,cjs,mjs,md,json,yaml}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md:\n  Line 25: Every `/memory:save` you trigger flows through `context-server.ts`, gets schema-validated, lands in a handler, fans out across 5 retrieval channels (vector, FTS5, BM25, causal graph, degree), and writes into a local SQLite store next to the rest of your repo. Every `/speckit:resume` reads from the same store and rebuilds your last session's context. Every prompt-submit hook in Claude, Codex, OpenCode, and Copilot calls into this package for its startup brief.\n\n  Line 36: - **The daemon-backed CLI.** `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool>` fronts all 39 tools over the daemon's IPC socket — the dual-stack surface for hooks, cron, CI and transport-down recovery. Exit taxonomy `0`/`1`/`64`/`69`/`75`; `--warm-only` probes instead of spawning; `list-tools` answers offline. Source: `spec-memory-cli.ts`.\n\n  Line 37: - **The plugin bridge.** The OpenCode plugin (`.opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js`) routes through `plugin_bridges/mk-spec-memory-bridge.mjs` using CLI transport only — it shells the same `spec-memory.cjs` front door rather than holding a second MCP connection.\n\n  Line 39: - **The compiled backend artifact.** `dist/context-server.js` is built by `npm run build` and spawned by the launcher. MCP client configs point at `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`, which supervises the backend and owns the client-facing transport. The MCP registrations themselves are unchanged by the CLI: dual-stack means the CLI is additive.\n\n  Line 64: │ MCP clients  │ ───▶ │ context-server.ts│ ───▶ │ tool dispatcher │\n\n  Line 92: +-- context-server.ts        # MCP transport entrypoint\n\n  Line 114: context-server.ts → tool-schemas.ts / tools/ → handlers/\n\n  Line 125: shared/ → handlers/ or context-server.ts\n\n  Line 152: +-- context-server.ts        # MCP server entrypoint\n\n  Line 165: | `context-server.ts` | Starts the MCP server, wires transport to the dispatcher, and enforces response token budgets. If first-call `meta.sessionPriming` pushes an envelope over budget, the server slims that metadata before dropping result rows. |\n\n  Line 166: | `spec-memory-cli.ts` | Daemon-backed CLI over the same 39 tools (built to `dist/spec-memory-cli.js`, fronted by `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs`). Parses per-tool flags against `tool-schemas.ts`, probes the daemon (warm-only honors exit `75`), auto-spawns the launcher otherwise, and maps errors to the `0`/`1`/`64`/`69`/`75` exit taxonomy. |\n\n  Line 192: | Public API | MCP tools are exposed through `tool-schemas.ts`, `tools/`, and `context-server.ts`. |\n\n  Line 210: │ context-server.ts                         │\n\n  Line 240: | `context-server.ts` | Module | Starts the MCP server from source or compiled output. |\n\n  Line 241: | `dist/context-server.js` | Runtime artifact | Compiled backend server spawned and supervised by the launcher. Client configuration points at `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`. |\n\n  Line 242: | `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool>` | CLI | Daemon-backed front door for all 39 tools (shim guards dist freshness, exit `69`; runs `dist/spec-memory-cli.js`). |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/context-server.ts:\n  Line 123: } from './lib/ipc/socket-server.js';\n\n  Line 351: // `dist/context-server.d.ts` declaration). The variable still drives the\n\n  Line 388:         console.error('[context-server] FTS5 shadow integrity-check failed; attempting boot auto-rebuild...');\n\n  Line 392:         console.error('[context-server] FTS5 shadow rebuilt and re-verified OK at boot.');\n\n  Line 398:           '[context-server] ===== FTS5 SHADOW INDEX CORRUPTION DETECTED =====',\n\n  Line 399:           '[context-server] Boot marker indicates the previous mk-spec-memory shutdown was unclean.',\n\n  Line 400:           `[context-server] FTS5 integrity-check failed: ${message}`,\n\n  Line 401:           `[context-server] Boot auto-rebuild FAILED: ${rebuildMessage}`,\n\n  Line 402:           '[context-server] DETECT-ONLY fallback: no further recovery attempted; manual repair required.',\n\n  Line 403:           `[context-server] Runbook: ${FTS_CORRUPTION_RUNBOOK}`,\n\n  Line 404:           '[context-server] =================================================',\n\n  Line 411:       '[context-server] ===== FTS5 SHADOW INDEX CORRUPTION DETECTED =====',\n\n  Line 412:       '[context-server] Boot marker indicates the previous mk-spec-memory shutdown was unclean.',\n\n  Line 413:       `[context-server] FTS5 integrity-check failed: ${message}`,\n\n  Line 414:       '[context-server] DETECT-ONLY: auto-heal disabled (SPECKIT_BOOT_FTS_AUTOHEAL=0); no rebuild attempted.',\n\n  Line 415:       `[context-server] Runbook: ${FTS_CORRUPTION_RUNBOOK}`,\n\n  Line 416:       '[context-server] =================================================',\n\n  Line 447:       console.error(`[context-server] Checkpoint derived rebuild repair (${source}) completed: completed=${completed}, failed=0, skipped=0`);\n\n  Line 450:         `[context-server] Checkpoint derived rebuild repair (${source}) incomplete; sentinel retained: completed=${completed}, failed=${failed}, skipped=${skipped}${result.error ? `, error=${result.error}` : ''}`,\n\n  Line 456:     console.warn(`[context-server] Checkpoint derived rebuild repair (${source}) failed (non-fatal): ${message}`);\n\n  Line 560:         console.error(`[context-server] afterTool callback failed for '${tool}' (${callId}): ${message}`);\n\n  Line 1013:     console.error(`[context-server] Failed to clear trigger cache after DB reinit: ${message}`);\n\n  Line 1017:     console.error(`[context-server] Cleared ${invalidatedEntries} tool-cache entries after DB reinitialization`);\n\n  Line 1107:         console.error(`[context-server] Session priming failed (non-fatal): ${msg}`);\n\n  Line 1128:           console.error(`[context-server] Auto-surface failed (non-fatal): ${msg}`);\n\n  Line 1136:         console.error(`[context-server] Tool-dispatch auto-surface failed (non-fatal): ${msg}`);\n\n  Line 1141:       console.warn(`[context-server] Auto-surface precheck exceeded p95 target: ${autoSurfaceLatencyMs}ms`);\n\n  Line 1239:         console.warn(`[context-server] Passive enrichment failed (non-fatal): ${msg}`);\n\n  Line 1367:       console.error(`[context-server] Failed to build MCP error envelope for '${name}': ${fallbackError}`);\n\n  Line 1429:   console.error('[context-server] Checking for pending memory files...');\n\n  Line 1462:       console.error(`[context-server] Pending file recovery: ${recoveryResult.recovered} recovered, ${recoveryResult.failed} failed (${recoveryResult.found} total)`);\n\n  Line 1464:       console.error('[context-server] No pending memory files found');\n\n  Line 1470:     console.error(`[context-server] Pending file recovery error: ${message}`);\n\n  Line 1477:     console.error('[context-server] Startup scan already in progress, skipping');\n\n  Line 1487:     console.error('[context-server] Starting background scan for spec documents and constitutional memories...');\n\n  Line 1518:       console.error('[context-server] No spec documents or constitutional memories found in workspace');\n\n  Line 1522:     console.error(`[context-server] Found ${allFiles.length} indexable files, checking for changes...`);\n\n  Line 1535:         console.error(`[context-server] Failed to index ${path.basename(filePath)}: ${message}`);\n\n  Line 1546:       console.error(`[context-server] Startup scan: ${indexed} new, ${updated} updated, ${unchanged} unchanged, ${failed} failed`);\n\n  Line 1548:       console.error(`[context-server] Startup scan: all ${unchanged} files up to date`);\n\n  Line 1568:       console.error(`[context-server] Atomicity metrics: ${metrics.totalAtomicWrites} successful, ${metrics.totalErrors} failed, ${metrics.totalRecoveries} recovered`);\n\n  Line 1572:     console.error(`[context-server] Startup scan error: ${message}`);\n\n  Line 1615:   console.error(`[context-server] ${reason}`);\n\n  Line 1695:     console.error(`[context-server] Shutdown deadline exceeded after ${SHUTDOWN_DEADLINE_MS}ms`);\n\n  Line 1784:     `[context-server] Detected runtime: ${detectedRuntime.runtime} (hookPolicy=${detectedRuntime.hookPolicy})`,\n\n  Line 1797:       console.error(`[context-server] ${error.message}`);\n\n  Line 1804:     console.error('[context-server] Initializing database...');\n\n  Line 1817:     console.error('[context-server] Database initialized');\n\n  Line 1818:     console.error('[context-server] Database path: ' + DATABASE_PATH);\n\n  Line 1831:         console.error(`[context-server] Pruned ${prunedReceipts} expired idempotency receipt(s)`);\n\n  Line 1841:         console.error(`[context-server] Admitted ${cold.admitted} archived/cold row(s) into the vector projection`);\n\n  Line 1849:       `[context-server] Active embedder: ${active.name} (${active.dim}d${active.provider ? `, ${active.provider}` : ''})`,\n\n  Line 1853:     console.error(`[context-server] FATAL: ${message}`);\n\n  Line 1865:     console.error('[context-server] Validating embedding API key...');\n\n  Line 1873:           console.warn('[context-server] ===== API KEY VALIDATION SKIPPED (network error) =====');\n\n  Line 1874:           console.warn(`[context-server] Provider: ${validation.provider}`);\n\n  Line 1875:           console.warn(`[context-server] Error: ${validation.error}`);\n\n  Line 1877:             console.warn('[context-server] Recovery Actions:');\n\n  Line 1879:               console.warn(`[context-server]   ${i + 1}. ${action}`);\n\n  Line 1882:           console.warn('[context-server] Continuing startup — validation will occur on first use');\n\n  Line 1884:           console.error('[context-server] ===== API KEY VALIDATION FAILED =====');\n\n  Line 1885:           console.error(`[context-server] Provider: ${validation.provider}`);\n\n  Line 1886:           console.error(`[context-server] Error: ${validation.error}`);\n\n  Line 1887:           console.error(`[context-server] Error Code: ${validation.errorCode || 'E050'}`);\n\n  Line 1889:             console.error('[context-server] Recovery Actions:');\n\n  Line 1891:               console.error(`[context-server]   ${i + 1}. ${action}`);\n\n  Line 1894:           console.error('[context-server] =====================================');\n\n  Line 1895:           console.error('[context-server] FATAL: Cannot start MCP server with invalid API key');\n\n  Line 1896:           console.error('[context-server] Set SPECKIT_SKIP_API_VALIDATION=true to bypass (not recommended)');\n\n  Line 1908:         console.warn(`[context-server] API key warning: ${validation.warning}`);\n\n  Line 1912:         console.error(`[context-server] API key validated (provider: ${validation.provider})`);\n\n  Line 1923:       console.error(`[context-server] API key validation error: ${message}`);\n\n  Line 1924:       console.error('[context-server] Continuing startup - validation will occur on first use');\n\n  Line 1927:     console.warn('[context-server] API key validation skipped (SPECKIT_SKIP_API_VALIDATION=true)');\n\n  Line 1956:   console.error('[context-server] Lazy loading enabled - embedding model will initialize on first use');\n\n  Line 1957:   console.error('[context-server] SPECKIT_EAGER_WARMUP and SPECKIT_LAZY_LOADING are deprecated compatibility flags');\n\n  Line 1962:     console.error(`[context-server] Integrity check: ${report.totalMemories}/${report.totalMemories + report.missingVectors} valid entries`);\n\n  Line 1963:     if (report.orphanedVectors > 0) console.error(`[context-server] WARNING: ${report.orphanedVectors} orphaned entries detected`);\n\n  Line 1968:       console.error(`[context-server] ===== EMBEDDING DIMENSION MISMATCH =====`);\n\n  Line 1969:       console.error(`[context-server] ${dimValidation.warning}`);\n\n  Line 1970:       console.error(`[context-server] =========================================`);\n\n  Line 1971:       console.error('[context-server] FATAL: Refusing to start with mismatched embedding dimensions');\n\n  Line 1974:       console.error(`[context-server] Embedding dimension validated: ${dimValidation.stored}`);\n\n  Line 1984:       console.error('[context-server] Scoring observability initialized');\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"context-server|model-server-supervision|socket-server|spec-memory.cjs","time":{"start":1781761475089,"end":1781761475172}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bd783c447d56089016a3385c2f39c81919b9cadc11bf5b8a4"}},"id":"prt_ed94281f9001CzGyz2W4bGWejL","sessionID":"ses_126bf2c73ffeZ1nadU7aA32XcF","messageID":"msg_ed942615d0018mOJ7KGSpgxLVx"}}
