{"type":"text","timestamp":1781761641737,"sessionID":"ses_126bf2c73ffeZ1nadU7aA32XcF","part":{"id":"prt_ed944f5c7001EW9aDmP1j3Dx51","messageID":"msg_ed944dca1001Zh7E4l7FT65Dk6","sessionID":"ses_126bf2c73ffeZ1nadU7aA32XcF","type":"text","text":"A second concrete candidate is checkpoint scope matching: the handler’s scope matcher treats missing checkpoint metadata as matching any requested tenant/user/agent scope, which may let scoped callers list/restore unscoped checkpoints. I’m opening the storage layer to confirm whether it is also filtered there or only in the handler.","time":{"start":1781761635783,"end":1781761641736},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06c8be0c896a84df016a338663c6888191815bfc7360da13b8","phase":"commentary"}}}}
